Durban - A heavy police presence remains in the KwaZulu-Natal rural town of Eshowe after violent protests erupted on Sunday. Angry mobs of people took to the streets and blocked off the R66 and P230. A farmhouse was also set alight and a bakkie stolen during the protests. 














