The farmhouse that was damaged during the fire. 
Video: Thami Magubane

According to police, they arrived just after 5pm to find debris strewn across the road. Officers managed to clear the area and the roads were re-opened to traffic. 
POP remained in the area on Monday in case of any more protests. 
Sunday's protests comes two months after violent clashes took place following the death of a 30-year old man. In March, Siphamandla Xulu was caught fishing on the Gqobhokani farm and was shot dead by a security guard. Incensed by the murder, residents protested. At least two farms were damaged when protesters set fire to crops. 
It is alleged that residents are unhappy that the security company is still employed in the town, despite March's shooting.














